                     </form>
                     <gramGrp opt="false">
                        <gram type="pos" opt="false">common noun</gram>
                     </gramGrp>
                     <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                        <quote>man</quote>
                     </cit>
                  </cit>
                  <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                     <form opt="false">
                        <orth opt="false">-λημψια</orth>
                     </form>
                     <gramGrp opt="false">
                        <gram type="pos" opt="false">common noun</gram>
                     </gramGrp>
                     <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                        <quote xml:lang="en">seizure</quote>
                     </cit>
                  </cit>
               </etym>
               <xr type="related" opt="false">
                  <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                  <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=a)ndrolhyi/a"
                       type="entry">ἀνδροληψία</ref>
               </xr>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               In 
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW I 124</bibl> explained as Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀνδρολυμασία</term>.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 143a</bibl>,
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 106b</bibl> (<term xml:lang="grc">ἀνδρολοιμός</term>);
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 81b</bibl> (<term xml:lang="grc">ἀνδρολημψία</term>). Löw (in LW II 598b) doubts Krauss’ explanation.
   </note>
